This presidential memorandum, issued on August 31, 2018, delegates certain authorities and functions under the Reinforcing Education Accountability in Development Act. The President delegates to the Secretary of State the functions and authorities vested in the President by sections 4, 6, and 7 of the READ Act. Additionally, the President delegates to the Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development the functions and authorities vested in the President by section 5(c) of the READ Act. The memorandum states that these delegations will also apply to any future public laws with provisions that are the same or substantially the same as those referenced in the memorandum. The Secretary of State or the Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development may redelegate these functions to the extent authorized by law. The Secretary of State is directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.